    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Shaare Zedek Medical Center</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Most pulmonologist request a routine chest-x-ray after bronchoscopy with transbronchial
      biopasie to exclude pneumothorax. We published a study in CHEST showing that routine
      chest-ray might not be necessary. We would like to conduct a propsective study to validate
      the results of the CHEST-study. Before and after the procedure follwing information will be
      collected: Age, Sex, Indication for procedure, number of biopsies and segment of biopsie,
      Saturation, Physical examination, Symptoms suggestive of pneumothorax. If there is no
      aggravation of the symptoms and/or physical examination after the procedure, as compared to
      before, routine chest-x-ray will NOT be done. A phone will be made 24 to 48 hours following
      the procedure to the patient.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
